        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:21PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Van, or 7 miles south of Madison, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Van, Danville, Sylvester, Seth, Turtle Creek, Prenter,
Ashford, Foster, Blair, Sharples, Racine, and Jeffrey.

This includes Route 119 between mile markers 44 and 53.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
